%N A217198 A list of odd primes p such that 2p-1 is prime and no p is equal to any 2q-1 with q in the sequence.
%C A217198 Sequence used in conjunction with A001259 in the referenced articles.
%C A217198 The article has 449 where this sequence has 499, which is likely a typo.
%C A217198 See A217199 for the lexicographically earliest sequence satisfying the same property.
%H A217198 A. Schinzel and Andrzej Wakulicz, <a href="http://matwbn.icm.edu.pl/ksiazki/aa/aa4/aa431.pdf">Sur l'équation phi(x+k)=phi(x), I.</a>, Acta Arith. 4 (1958), 181-184.
